Media

Class Sound

  • java.lang.Object
    • Media.Sound
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Sample>

    public class Sound
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<Sample>
    This class represents a sound that can be played. A sound is a collection of Samples, being the height of the sound wave at the sampling intervals. A sound can be saved as a WAV file.
    Version:
    1.0 July 2008, 2.0 (08/07/09), 3.0 (09/05/04), 4.0 (09/05/04), 5.0 (10/09/02), 6.0 (12/06/12)
    Author:
    A. Cheesman, D. Hughes, D. Hughes, D. Hughes, D. Hughes, D. Hughes
